   "source": [
    "# Reporting Disease Frequency in Clinical Research: Incidence and Prevalence\n",
    "\n",
    "**Authors:** Renato Carneiro de Freitas Chaves, Tiago Mendonça dos Santos, Thiago Domingos Corrêa"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a6e8ca4b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Purpose\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook provides a step-by-step analytical structure for **clinical research** comparing:\n",
    "- **Control group** (`group = 0`)\n",
    "- **Intervention group** (`group = 1`)\n",
    "\n",
    "Using the attached dataset, it demonstrates how to estimates and interprets four:\n",
    "1. incidence proportion.\n",
    "2. incidence rate\n",
    "3. Prevalence\n",
    "4. At-risk population.\n",
    "\n",
    "The dataset contains individual-level intensive care unit clinical information. Hospital mortality at discharge is represented by `outcome = 1`. Follow-up-based events are represented by `event = 1` and are used for person-time analyses.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Dataset coding**\n",
    "\n",
    "- `group`: `0 = Control`, `1 = Intervention`\n",
    "- `outcome`: `0 = Alive`, `1 = Dead`\n",
    "- Binary comorbidity and support variables: `0 = No`, `1 = Yes`\n",
    "- `mechanical_ventilation`: invasive mechanical ventilation at ICU admission\n",
    "- `vasopressor`: vasopressor use at ICU admission\n",
    "\n",
    "**Analytical note:** `outcome` is a time-independent status at hospital discharge, whereas `event` is a time-dependent occurrence during follow-up.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e82067ef",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
